-- Alon Surges to Two-Year High After Israel Oil Increases Stake
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-04-30T13:57:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/alon-surges-to-two-year-high-after-israel-oil-increases-stake.html
Alon Natural Gas Exploration Ltd. (ALGS) 
advanced to the highest in more than two years after the natural
gas company’s controlling shareholder increased its ownership.  The  shares  rose 6.3 percent to 43.80 shekels, the highest
level since February 2010, at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  “Alon” Israel Oil Co. increased its stake to 82.77
percent by buying 115,000 shares at 43.71 shekels each,
according to a filing with the Tel-Aviv Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
